title: PMLN’s Anwar ul Haq Chaudary wins NA-75 election
content:
ISLAMABAD, Feb 9 (APP): Pakistan Muslim League Nawaz (PMLN) Anwar ul Haq Chaudary has won the election for National Assembly constituency NA-75, Narowal I by securing 99,625 votes.
According to the unofficial result issued by the Returning Officer/ECP, his runner-up was Independent Candidate Tahir Ali Javed, who bagged 75,626 votes.
Overall voters’ turn-out remained 51.56 percent.
